metadata.editComments: Perhaps that was a harsh term to use, but I did not agree with a single one of those edits, outside of the spelling of a diminished i chord instead of the full functional chord since it's easier to read. Plus, the forced in key change screwed up the breaks in the sections. I honestly initially thought these edits were the results of griefing, so I apologize for the blunt, annoyed, response. But to speak to your changes, I do not believe any portion of this is in the Dorian mode. There are no chords supporting this raised 6th in the scale, outside of the G natural in the instrumental, but this is a functional diminished chord which requires an altered Dorian scale specifically when vamping over that chord. That does not make the section IN the Dorian mode, however. I hope that makes sense. Feel free to refute these changes with theory, but I will defend my choices if prompted. Thank you :) Sorry again.
